<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-549] ConsumerOffsetChecker does not deal with hostnames published in zookeeper</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-549</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When configuring the broker using the &apos;hostname=&apos; property in server.properties to publish hostnames in zookeeper, the ConsumerOffsetChecker can&apos;t parse the hostname from the zknode&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attached patch changes the host regexp to match hostnames as well as ip addresses.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
